</section>

<section id="projects" class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <h2>Selected case studies & projects</h2>
    <p>Examples that reflect how I think and work. Honest about constraints; focused on lessons and value.</p>
    
    <div class="grid-3" style="margin-top:16px">
      
      <article class="project">
        <div class="project-header">
          <div class="project-icon-wrap" style="--ox:-2px;--oy:-3px;" aria-label="Icon for innovative toy venture">
            <img src="https://adriankordowski.pl/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/icon1_cropped.png" alt="Icon" />
          </div>
          <strong>High-risk Toy Venture — Critical Financial & Operational Analysis</strong>
        </div>
        <p>Client approached me with extremely optimistic projections: over €315M revenue in 24 months, 50M+ units sold and ≈963% ROI — based on less than two pages of raw assumptions.</p>
        <p>I rebuilt the entire market, cost and logistics model from scratch, iterating it more than ten times to keep it internally consistent while clearly documenting why the input assumptions remained unrealistic for any serious investor.</p>
        <p class="small"><span class="label">Key metrics:</span> ~270h analysis · &lt;2 pages initial data · 50M+ units &amp; 200k/day sales assumption (client-driven).</p>
        <p class="small"><span class="label">Lesson:</span> separate professional judgment from client expectations, and keep your modeling standards even when the numbers you're given don't add up.</p>
        <a class="view-link" href="https://adriankordowski.pl/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/Businessplan-Adrian-Kordowski.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
          <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none"><path d="M5 12h14M13 5l7 7-7 7" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round"/></svg>
          view full business plan (PDF)
        </a>
      </article>

      <article class="project">
        <div class="project-header">
          <div class="project-icon-wrap" style="--ox:-1px;--oy:-4px;" aria-label="Icon for self-storage project">
            <img src="https://adriankordowski.pl/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/icon3_cropped.png" alt="Icon" />
          </div>
          <strong>Self-Storage Venture — Full Case Study</strong>
        </div>
        <p>Advanced to Phase 2 with a maximum innovation score after building the concept end-to-end: market research, strategy, business plan, and financial model.</p>
        <p>The case study shows how I built the business case end-to-end — and how I’d strengthen the evidence layer today (benchmarking, assumptions, and financial validation) to make it investor-ready.</p>
        <p class="small"><span style="color:var(--accent); font-weight:600">Key metrics:</span> competitor footprint &amp; density, price bands by location, staffing model per site, digital acquisition intensity.<br><span style="color:var(--accent); font-weight:600">Lesson:</span> research must go beyond desk data — benchmarking top players reveals what actually drives performance and where the inefficiencies hide.</p>
        <a class="view-link" href="https://adriankordowski.pl/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/Self-Storage_Case_Study_Adrian-Kordowski_v2.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
          <span aria-hidden="true">→</span> view full case study (PDF)
        </a>
      </article>

      <article class="project">
        <div class="project-header">
          <div class="project-icon-wrap" style="--ox:-4px;--oy:-2px;" aria-label="Icon for modular houses project">
            <img src="https://adriankordowski.pl/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/icon2_cropped.png" alt="Icon" />
          </div>
          <strong>Modular Housing — Strategic R&D & Efficiency Analysis</strong>
        </div>
        <p>Partnered with a modular construction firm capable of rapid 1-week assembly to secure government funding (>€1M) and drive national-scale innovation.</p>
        <p>I conducted a comprehensive financial and operational audit, identifying critical material improvements and proposing CNC automation to maximize production efficiency. The strategy also included structuring an R&D partnership with a technical university.</p>
        <p class="small"><strong style="color: #4ade80; display: inline;">Key metrics:</strong> >€1M funding scope · National-scale R&D strategy · 1-week assembly model analyzed.</p>
        <p class="small"><strong style="color: #4ade80; display: inline;">Lesson:</strong> Seemingly minor constraints often dictate the business model. I found that road transport height regulations forced us to split modules into two shipments, drastically altering logistics costs.</p>
      </article>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>

